<rss xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/" version="2.0"><channel><title>NBC News Top Stories</title><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/</link><description>NBC News Top Stories</description><language>en-US</language><copyright>© 2026 NBCNews.com</copyright><lastBuildDate>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 22:21:41 GMT</lastBuildDate><image><url>https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/MSNBC/Components/Media/NBC-promo-graphics/nbc-news.png</url><title>NBC News Top Stories</title><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/</link></image><item><dc:creator>Gordon Lubold</dc:creator><dc:creator>Courtney Kube</dc:creator><dc:creator>Dan De Luce</dc:creator><dc:creator>Monica Alba</dc:creator><dc:contributor>Abigail Williams</dc:contributor><dateTimeWritten>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 22:21:41 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Iran is taking advantage of the ceasefire with the U.S. to dig out its weapons, according to a U.S. official and two other people familiar with the matter.</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/white-house/iran-accelerating-efforts-dig-missiles-munitions-rcna342881</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/white-house/iran-accelerating-efforts-dig-missiles-munitions-rcna342881</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-03/260306-missile-launched-from-iran-ew-1205p-975fb4.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Eyad Baba</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Image: A missile launched from Iran in the sky, viewed from the Bureij camp for Palestinian refugees in the central Gaza Strip</media:text><media:description type="plain">A missile launched from Iran as seen from the central Gaza Strip on March 1.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-03/260304-missile-Qamishli-International-Airport-rs-d87307.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Orhan Qereman</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Iranian missile falls near Qamishli International Airport</media:text><media:description type="plain">A missile launched from Iran as seen from the central Gaza Strip on March 1.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-03/260306-missile-launched-from-iran-ew-1205p-975fb4.jpg" height="1667" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 22:21:41 GMT</pubDate><title>Iran is accelerating efforts to dig out missiles and munitions</title><updateDate>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 22:21:41 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Ryan Nobles</dc:creator><dc:creator>Monica Alba</dc:creator><dc:creator>Alexandra Marquez</dc:creator><dc:contributor>Amanda Terkel</dc:contributor><dc:contributor>Raquel Coronell Uribe</dc:contributor><dateTimeWritten>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 14:47:10 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>House Speaker Mike Johnson, R-La., said Thursday that it is not necessary for Congress to weigh in on the Trump administration’s military action in Iran because the United States is currently “not at war.”“I don’t think we have an active, kinetic military bombing, firing or anything like that.</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/congress/house-speaker-mike-johnson-says-us-not-war-iran-white-house-approaches-rcna342868</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/congress/house-speaker-mike-johnson-says-us-not-war-iran-white-house-approaches-rcna342868</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-04/260430-mike-johnson-vl-952a-6f437e.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1334" width="2000"><media:credit>Heather Diehl</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Mike Johnson</media:text><media:description type="plain">Speaker of the House Mike Johnson, R-La., at the U.S. Capitol on March 3, 2026.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-04/260430-mike-johnson-vl-952a-6f437e.jpg" height="1334" width="2000"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 14:47:10 GMT</pubDate><title>Mike Johnson says U.S. &#39;not at war&#39; with Iran as key deadline nears</title><updateDate>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 20:20:23 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Scott Wong</dc:creator><dc:creator>Melanie Zanona</dc:creator><dc:creator>Kyle Stewart</dc:creator><dc:contributor>Brennan Leach</dc:contributor><dc:contributor>Lizzie Jensen</dc:contributor><dateTimeWritten>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 16:30:16 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>In addition to the DHS funding bill, President Donald Trump also signed into law a short-term extension of the foreign spy program known as FISA.</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/congress/congress-expected-end-record-75-day-partial-government-shutdown-rcna342903</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/congress/congress-expected-end-record-75-day-partial-government-shutdown-rcna342903</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-04/260417-capitol-hill-ch-1528-1fd938.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1667" width="2500"><media:credit>Alex Wroblewski</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Capitol exterior.</media:text><media:description type="plain">Homeland Security Secretary Markwayne Mullin had warned lawmakers that if they didn&#39;t pass funding by Thursday, emergency funding would run out and thousands of workers wouldn&#39;t be paid.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-04/260417-capitol-hill-ch-1528-1fd938.jpg" height="1667" width="2500"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 16:30:16 GMT</pubDate><title>Record-long Department of Homeland Security shutdown ends</title><updateDate>Fri, 01 May 2026 00:27:53 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dateTimeWritten>Thu, 30 Apr 2026 23:33:52 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>The Department of Justice released new video that shows the suspect in the White House Correspondents’ Dinner shooting running through the security checkpoint and appearing to point his weapon at a Secret Service agent. NBC News’ Kelly O’Donnell breaks down the new images.</description><expires>2056-04-30T23:33:10.000+0000</expires><guid isPermaLink="false">now_topstory_kod_suspect_video_260430</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/video/white-house-correspondents-dinner-suspect-seen-running-through-security-in-new-video-262493765914</link><media:content url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/now_topstory_kod_suspect_video_260430/1/abs/index.m3u8" medium="video"><media:credit></media:credit><media:title>DOJ releases new video showing Correspondents’ Dinner suspect running through security</media:title><media:player url="https://www.nbcnews.com/video/white-house-correspondents-dinner-suspect-seen-running-through-security-in-new-video-262493765914"></media:player><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/mpx/2704722219/2026_04/1777591980386_now_topstory_kod_suspect_video_260430_S3_1920x1080-50rupr.jpg"></media:thumbnail><media:description type="plain">The Department of Justice released new video that shows the suspect in the White House Correspondents’ Dinner shooting running through the security checkpoint and appearing to point his weapon at a Secret Service agent. NBC News’ Kelly O’Donnell breaks down the new images.</media:description><media:subTitle type="text/srt" lang="en-US" url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/nbcnews/captions/2026/04/1777591980386_now